Text.Value: A new client? What a thrill - for you, rat-urally!
What sort of items does the Great Collector collect?
Some call me the Great Collector. Others, the Merchant of Mysteries. But you, my friend...
Artefacts most priceless, should one call a prison his home.
Artefacts most priceless, should one call a prison her home.
Artefacts most priceless, should one call a prison their home.
It must be difficult to obtain goods in a prison. What does that en-tail?
Step up and let Skittle sort you out.
What's for sale? I'd like to take a squeak.
*Squeak.*
*Squrrk.*
*Chk-chk-chk.*
Captives have wants and needs. It is my pleasure - nay, my duty - to fulfil them.
Leave.
Aw. As you wish.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sweetly sad - player has asked the rat to make no more puns

Text.Value: Let me have a look at your stock.
My enterprise is of a more... covert sort. I do my dealings in squeak-ret.
A mercantile rodent? How rat-ical!
It must be difficult to obtain goods in a prison. What does that en-tail?
Step up and marvel at the spec-rat-ular wonders on offer!
...you can call me Skittle.
Let's take a squeak at what you've got.
Is rat all?
Captives have wants and needs, my pun-tifal patron. It is my pleasure - nay, my duty - to fulfil them.
Indeed, my mirthful mate. Care to take a squeak at my fan-rats-tical wares?
Is this business rat-ified by the local merchant's league?
Enough rat puns. Show me your inventory.
Brilliant. Anything more?
The prison's pipes are a veritable maze of cracks and crannies. What a rat finds, a rat keeps.
No more puns, all right?

Synopsis: This is a rat who lives in LOW prison. Over a long period of time it bartered with numerous prisoners and stole stuff from dead and from evidence/confiscation stash.
